# Cross-Platform Parity (Mac + Windows)

Custody Note is **one app with two builds** (macOS DMG/ZIP, Windows NSIS). User-visible custody workflow behaviour must be identical on both platforms.

## Required parity

These must match on macOS and Windows:

- Renderer UI and business logic (`app.js`, `renderer/views/*.js`)
- Preload and main IPC API — no new platform-gated methods for shared features
- Database, backup, licence, attendance, exports, security lock
- Outlook Web email — same compose URL and single execution path (Windows browser bypass in `lib/openExternalUrl.js` is OK; outcome must be the same)
- Auto-update user experience (check, prompt, install) — install mechanics may differ

## Mandatory workflow when changing code

1. Grep for `process.platform`, `win32`, `darwin`, `platform !==`, `platform ===` in touched areas
2. **Do not** add platform branches for custody or business logic — implement one shared path
3. If a platform branch is unavoidable, it must be OS integration only, commented, and on the allowlist below
4. In completion notes, explicitly state **Mac impact** and **Windows impact**

## Allowed platform-specific code (allowlist)

Do not expand this list without explicit user approval:

- Path roots and `userData` resolution (`main.js` — `getFallbackAppDataRoot`)
- macOS application menu (`main.js` — `buildMacAppMenu`)
- Windows App User Model ID, desktop shortcut IPC, Outlook AppX bypass (`lib/openExternalUrl.js`)
- Updater install teardown on Windows (`updater.js` — `app.exit(0)` after `quitAndInstall`)
- electron-builder `win` / `mac` config, NSIS vs DMG, `latest.yml` vs `latest-mac.yml`
- UI copy referencing OS credential store; hide Windows-only controls on Mac (`app.js` — shortcut button, PIN tip)

## Forbidden

- Mac-only or Windows-only custody features without explicit user request
- Different business rules, form behaviour, or data paths per platform
- Renderer platform checks for core custody workflows
- Parallel implementations of the same feature per platform

## Verification checklist (before finishing)

- Change works on both platforms, or is on the allowlist above
- No new IPC/preload surface gated to one platform for shared features
- Tests updated if behaviour changes; follow parity-test pattern in `tests/preloadOutlookWebComposeParity.test.js`
